(x^2-x^5)\frac{1}{(1-x)^3}  \\= (x^2-x^5)\sum_{i=0}^\infty {-3 \choose i}(-x)^i \\= (x^2-x^5)\sum_{i=0}^\infty {-3 \choose i}(-1)^ix^i \\= (x^2-x^5)\sum_{i=0}^\infty {3+i-1 \choose i}x^i 
{-3 \choose i}(-1)^i
{3+i-1\choose i}
k
i
\displaystyle \binom{n}k
\dfrac{n(n-1)\dots(n-k+1)}{k!}
\binom{-3}k = \frac{(-3)(-4)\dots(-3-k+1)}{k!} = \frac{(-1)^k(3+k-1)\dots(4)(3)}{k!} = (-1)^k\binom{3+k-1}{k}
(-1)^k\binom{-3}{k} = \binom{3 + k - 1}{k}.
\binom{-n}{k} = (-1)^k \binom{n + k - 1}{k}.
